description:
Are you a data enthusiast with experience in data warehousing, data pipelines & ETL/ELT? Want to play a key role in building a modern and scalable data architecture in a growing team? Do you want to be part of our journey and want to work in an international environment?

Refresco is the world's largest independent bottler of beverages for leading retailers and A-brands with production in Europe... North America and Mexico. Slightly over 140 people work at the head office in Rotterdam, versus more than 11,000 employees elsewhere in the world. Confidence in the strength of good, local teams is a hallmark of Refresco's approach to the business. The teams make decisions in close collaboration with the central team but have a large sense of ownership choosing the best approach for their local market.
The desire to continue growing is reflected across every layer of the organization. This translates into an extremely enterprising group of people who are constantly setting new things in motion and really want to make an impact. A focus on personal growth and development is a priority at Refresco.

Information Technology and digitalization are increasingly important to realize synergies in the organization and drive a high-quality customer experience across Refresco. Therefore, has Refresco embarked on a journey to modernize and rationalize our data and IT architecture across Refresco Europe.

Data Analyst / Modeler

As a Data Analyst/Modeler you play an essential role in enabling the vision of our Enterprise Data Strategy as a part of the Enterprise Data Team within Central IT Europe.
The Data Analyst/ Modeler is responsible for the translation of business requirements into conceptual & logical data models that are linked to physical data models in Refresco’s cloud data warehouse.

Refresco values innovation & entrepreneurship and fresh ideas are always welcome. As a Data Modeler, you keep yourself informed & updated on the trends in your area of expertise with the aim of continuous improvement.
With this mandate, coupled with a deep knowledge of the systems & processes involved, you are responsible for the design, deployment & change management in your area.
We are looking for a problem solver who is not afraid to take responsibility. In short, you are always looking for ways to do things better.

Central IT for Europe is a team of over 25 members, divided in 4 functional teams.
The team of Enterprise Data Management has IT Specialists focusing on Master Data Management, Data Analytics, EAI & EDI and is a multi-cultural team comprising of 6 colleagues. You will report into the Lead for BI & EAI.

Your Responsibilities:

Data modeling & data model ownership

• Work along with the Lead, BI & EAI to design & maintain an overview of the common data model for the Data Platform.
• You play a decisive role in implementing a Cloud Data Platform and its associated data pipelines
• You own the “Transform” step in the E-T-L process with a focus on professionalizing and optimizing the Data transformation flow.

Requirements analysis & delivering changes:

• Along with a Data Engineer and Analytics/BI specialists, you analyze business requirements related to Reporting, and offer possibilities to use the data platform to fulfil the analytics requirement.
• You are responsible for proposing, implementing & documenting the Data Model for the requirement – always keeping an overview of the common virtual data model.
• The system configuration is your accountability; you may do it yourself or delegate it on an external partner.

Change Management, Governance & Improvement:

• Being responsible for incidents & change requests, you have an external support team whom you will coordinate.
• You work with the team on their journey towards DevOps (e.g., CI/CD).
• You ensure that the performance & scaling of the Data models is always optimum.

What you offer:
• Bachelor’s or Master’s Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or other fields related to the role, or equivalent experience;
• Excellent knowledge of SQL, Data Warehousing and ETL technologies ;
• At least 4-5 years of professional experience with;
• Strong understanding of Data Modeling concepts;
• Experience on cloud data warehouse solutions such as Snowflake (or comparable technologies);
• Proven experience in the development, validation, publishing and maintaining conceptual & logical data models and their relationship with physical data models;
• Experience in SAP ERP systems is a plus;
• Experience working in Azure, or a Microsoft-specific environment is a plus;
• Working experience on DevOps (e.g., CI/CD) is a plus
• Working experience on Data Transformation tools such as dbt is a plus
• Experience with Data Modelling tools (Erwin, Enterprise Architect) is a plus
• Good written, oral and presentation skills;
• Fluent in English. Willingness to learn Dutch;
• You are eager to work in an informal, international, and entrepreneurial environment in a fast-growing company;
• You enjoy driving decisions with various stakeholders.

Linked to our company values, we work with a set of core competencies:
• Vision;
• Entrepreneurship;
• Group Leadership;
• Coaching;
• Result Orientation;
• Team Work;
• Behavioural Flexibility

Recruitment process

